.TH man_1_simple_shell 1 "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
man_1_simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B man_1_simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is a basic command line interpreter that allows users to execute commands.

.PP
The shell supports the following features:
.TP
\- Execute basic commands
\- Handle command lines with arguments
\- Locate executables in the PATH

.SH USAGE
Start the shell by running:
.PP
.B man_1_simple_shell

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns 0 on success and non-zero on failure.

.SH AUTHORS
The Simple Shell project is maintained by Saleh Shahverdiyev <salehsahverdiyev201@gmail.com> and Gunel Sultanova <gunel.sultanova@outlook.com>

.SH REPORTING BUGS
Report any bugs to the GitHub repository: https://github.com/salehshahverdiyev/holbertonschool-simple_shell/issues
